body:
@ngupta23 Exactly my point. I do not think the blame is on splitters themselves. I understand that, despite the explicit wish of a user for a non-full range forecasting horizon, cross-validation, especially with exogenous variables, should be performed on the full range test window. As you have discovered yourself, the solution should not be implemented on splitters side, but on evaluation and cross-validation side, like in the reference you gave above.

Another solution would be completely on a user's side. He/she should provide a full-range forecasting horizon and subset the results to only those horizons that are of interest. But I guess I am expecting too much ;)

Ok, given the link you referenced, is the issue still open?
